<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-13T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–947: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-13T12:00:00-05:00">March 13,
                                1947—noon</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>300. In order to correct possible ambiguity in Deptel 292 Mar 10, executive
                        order mentioned paragraph 3 does not touch upon activities of NAG but deals
                        solely with transfer of ships.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>